"""---
## 4. Lexicon Selection Justification

| Lexicon | Selected | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| **VADER** | ✅ | Built for informal/social text; handles !!!, CAPS, negations natively |
| **TextBlob** | ✅ | Pattern-based; outputs polarity + subjectivity; complementary to VADER |
| SentiWordNet | ❌ | Requires POS tagging + sense disambiguation; too noisy for informal reviews |

---
## 5. Pre-Processing Pipelines

| Step | VADER | TextBlob | Reason |
|---|---|---|---|
| Lowercase | No | Yes | VADER uses caps as intensity signal |
| Remove HTML/URLs | Yes | Yes | Pure noise |
| Remove punctuation | No | Yes | VADER uses `!!!` as amplifier |
| Remove stopwords | No | Yes | VADER needs negations ("not bad"); TextBlob benefits from noise reduction |
| Lemmatization | No | Yes | Helps TextBlob match its lexicon |
"""

stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))
lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()

def clean_vader(text):
    text = re.sub(r'<[^>]+>', ' ', text)
    text = re.sub(r'http\S+|www\.\S+', ' ', text)
    return re.sub(r'\s+', ' ', text).strip()

def clean_textblob(text):
    text = re.sub(r'<[^>]+>', ' ', text)
    text = re.sub(r'http\S+|www\.\S+', ' ', text)
    text = text.lower()
    text = re.sub(r'[^a-z\s]', ' ', text)
    tokens = word_tokenize(text)
    tokens = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(t) for t in tokens
              if t not in stop_words and len(t) > 1]
    return ' '.join(tokens)

print('Processing VADER text...')
df['text_vader'] = df['combined_text'].apply(clean_vader)
print('Processing TextBlob text...')
df['text_textblob'] = df['combined_text'].apply(clean_textblob)

